{{COI|date=November 2014}} {{More citations needed|date=March 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox university | name = Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata | native_name = | image_name = IISER-K Logo.svg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | motto = Towards Excellence in Science for an Innovative India | mottoeng = | established = 2006 | closed = | type = [[Public]] | affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | rector = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = [[Prathap C. Reddy]] | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | principal = | dean = | director = [[Sourav Pal]] | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = 1204<ref>http://students.iiserkol.ac.in/</ref> | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Haringhata]], [[Mohanpur, Nadia|Mohanpur]] (Transient) | state = [[West Bengal]] | province = | country = [[India]] | coor = {{Coord|22.963767|88.524613|type:edu|display=inline,title}} | campus = Rural, 201 acres | former_names = | free_label = | free = | athletics = | colours = | colors = | sports = | nickname = | mascot = | website = {{url|http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/}} | logo = | footnotes = | affiliations = }}
'''Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata''' ('''IISER-K''' or '''IISER - Kolkata''') is an autonomous science research and education [[institute]] in [[Nadia district]], [[West Bengal]], India, awarding its own degrees. It was established by the [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]] in 2006 and promoted to the status of an Institute of National Importance in 2012 vide the NIT Amendment Act.<ref>[http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/images/iiserk/announcements/nit_amendment_act_2012.pdf NIT Amendment Act, 2012]</ref> It is one of seven [[Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research]], and was the first of the IISERs to be established along with IISER Pune.
==Admissions== Admission is done through 3 channels for all IISERs<ref>url="https://www.iiseradmission.in/?page_id=25" Retrieved 4 October 2018</ref>. # KVPY channel # JEE Main/Advance Channel # SCB Channel
Students applying through SCB have to be in top 1 percentile scorers of their respective board examination (+2 level). After qualifying this Eligibility, students have to appear for Common IISER Aptitude Test, through score of this test, students are allotted their preferred IISER.
== Organisation == The institute has five major departments: [[biological science]]s; [[chemical science]]s; [[earth science]]s; [[mathematics]] and [[statistics]]; and [[physical science]]s.<ref>[http://www.iiserkol.ac.in/dean-academics/departments Departments at IISER Kolkata]</ref>
The institute hosts the Centre of Excellence for Space Sciences (CESSI)<ref>[http://cessi.iiserkol.ac.in/ CESSI IISER Kolkata]</ref> and a Max Planck-DST Partner Group of Chemical Ecology funded by the [[Max Planck Society]].{{citation needed|date=April 2016}} It also has a field station for ecological, environmental and field studies, and a broadband [[seismological observatory]]. {{citation needed|date=April 2016}} The institute jointly runs the Göttingen-Kolkata: Open shell systems (G-KOSS) in fundamentals of [[molecular spintronics]] with [[Georg-August-Universität Göttingen]].<ref>[http://www.uni-goettingen.de/en/195215.html Georg-August-Universität Göttingen - Göttingen-Kolkata: G-KOSS]. Uni-goettingen.de (2013-07-07). Retrieved on 2013-10-09.</ref>
==Events== The college organizes a major annual festival, Inquivesta,<ref>[http://www.inquivesta.iiserkol.ac.in/ Inquivesta Home Page]</ref> which is promoted as one of the first and the biggest science fest of the country. IISER Kolkata has also been hosting VIJYOSHI (the national science camp), along with IISc Bangalore and the Department of Science and Technology, Govt. of India, since 2014.
== Rankings == {{Infobox India university ranking | type = University | NIRF_O_2018 = 25 }}
Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, Kolkata was ranked 25 by the [[National Institutional Ranking Framework]] in overall ranking in 2018.<ref name=Rankings_NIRF_O_2018/>
