{{Infobox journal | title = Jewish Bible Quarterly | cover = Jewish Bible Quarterly.jpg | image_size = 150px | editor = Zvi Ron | discipline = [[Hebrew Bible]] | abbreviation = | former_name = Dor le Dor | language = English | publisher = Jewish Bible Association | country = Israel | history = 1972-present | frequency = Quarterly | website = http://jbq.jewishbible.org | link1 = | link1-name = | ISSN = 0792-3910 | LCCN = | OCLC = 21320204 |JSTOR = }} The '''''Jewish Bible Quarterly''''' is a journal about the [[Hebrew Bible]]. It is published by the Jewish Bible Association. The editor is Rabbi Dr. Zvi Ron.
''JBQ'' was established in 1972 as ''Dor le Dor''. It was published by the [[Jewish Bible Society|World Jewish Bible Society]], and edited by Louis Katzoff. It was established as the English-language publication of the society, whereas ''[[Beit Mikra]]'' was the Hebrew-language publication covering the same subject area.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Halpern |first1=Joseph |title=Tribute to Ben Zion Luria |journal=[[Dor le Dor]] |date=1983 |volume=10|issue=3|page=142|url= http://jbq.jewishbible.org/assets/Uploads/10/jbq_10_3_final.pdf |accessdate=7 December 2015}}</ref> Dr. Shimon Bakon was the editor from 1987 until 2011. He currently serves as editor emeritus.
